				\begin{document}$$_\mathrm{{LARGE}}$$\end{document} feature-based approach where the LM is not fine-tuned and its last four hidden layers are concatenated. Flair [1] uses a character-level LM for contextualization. As in ELMo, they train two opposite LSTM LMs, freeze them and concatenate the predicted states of the first and last characters of each word. Flair and ELMo are pretrained on the 1 Billion Word Benchmark [3] while BERT uses Book Corpus [22] and English Wikipedia.

